                            "identifier": "sonia_sotomayor"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 23.98,
                                "byte_start": 104448,
                                "byte_stop": 200370,
                                "text": "In the first case, at the time of petitioner Frantz DePierre\u0027s conviction in sentence, clause (iii) of 21 U.S.C. 841 (b)(1)(a), provided a mandatory ten-year minimum sentence for certain drug offenses involving 50 grams or more of a mixture or substance which contains cocaine base."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 23.98,
                                "stop": 32.958,
                                "byte_start": 200370,
                                "byte_stop": 236314,
                                "text": "DePierre, was convicted by a jury of distributing 50 grams or more of cocaine base, and he was sentence to ten years in prison."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 32.958,
                                "stop": 51.102,
                                "byte_start": 236314,
                                "byte_stop": 308935,
                                "text": "This case presents the question whether the term \u0022cocaine base\u0022 in clause subdivision (iii) refers to the chemically basic form of cocaine as the government who argues, or whether it refers strictly to crack cocaine as DePierre would have it."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 51.102,
                                "stop": 56.524,
                                "byte_start": 308935,
                                "byte_stop": 330564,
                                "text": "Cocaine is a chemically basic compound derived from the coca plant."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 56.524,
                                "stop": 62.014,
                                "byte_start": 330564,
                                "byte_stop": 352507,
                                "text": "The leaves of which can be processed into a smokable paste-like substance."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 62.014,
                                "stop": 75.184,
                                "byte_start": 352507,
                                "byte_stop": 405274,
                                "text": "When this coca paste is processed with hydrochloric acid, the result is cocaine hydrochloride, the powder form of cocaine which is most commonly snorted."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 75.184,
                                "stop": 78.525,
                                "byte_start": 405274,
                                "byte_stop": 418649,
                                "text": "Cocaine hydrochloride is not a base."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 78.525,
                                "stop": 84.877,
                                "byte_start": 418649,
                                "byte_stop": 444040,
                                "text": "It is a salt with a different molecular formula than chemically basic cocaine."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 84.877,
                                "stop": 96.336,
                                "byte_start": 444040,
                                "byte_stop": 489806,
                                "text": "However, it can be converted into chemically basic cocaine by processing it with a base like baking soda, producing crack cocaine which is smoked."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 96.336,
                                "stop": 106.008,
                                "byte_start": 489806,
                                "byte_stop": 528572,
                                "text": "Cocaine hydrochloride can also be processed with ammonia to produce a less common smokable drug known as \u0022freebase\u0022."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 106.008,
                                "stop": 114.07,
                                "byte_start": 528572,
                                "byte_stop": 560755,
                                "text": "Coca paste, crack cocaine, and freebase, all contain cocaine in its basic form."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 114.07,
                                "stop": 122.918,
                                "byte_start": 560755,
                                "byte_stop": 596177,
                                "text": "We agree with the government that the most natural reading of the term \u0022cocaine base\u0022 is chemically basic cocaine."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 122.918,
                                "stop": 137.067,
                                "byte_start": 596177,
                                "byte_stop": 652810,
                                "text": "In arguing that the term should be read instead to mean only crack cocaine, DePierre asked so as to stray far from the statute\u0027s text, as the term \u0022crack cocaine\u0022 appears nowhere in the statute."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 137.067,
                                "stop": 144.749,
                                "byte_start": 652810,
                                "byte_stop": 683530,
                                "text": "Although the term \u0022cocaine base\u0022 is somewhat redundant, from a chemical prospective, cocaine is a base."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 144.749,
                                "stop": 162.598,
                                "byte_start": 683530,
                                "byte_stop": 754897,
                                "text": "We think Congress had good reason to use cocaine in clause (iii), namely to distinguish the substances covered by that clause from the cocaine related substances enumerated in another clause in the statute, which provides lower penalties."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 162.598,
                                "stop": 173.907,
                                "byte_start": 754897,
                                "byte_stop": 800141,
                                "text": "At the time Congress enacted the statute, the word \u0022cocaine\u0022 was commonly used to refer simply to cocaine hydrochloride that is powder cocaine."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 173.907,
                                "stop": 186.068,
                                "byte_start": 800141,
                                "byte_stop": 848729,
                                "text": "And in the scientific and medical literature, if it wasn\u0027t confusing enough, the word \u0022cocaine\u0022 is often used to refer to all cocaine related substances including powder cocaine."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 186.068,
                                "stop": 194.537,
                                "byte_start": 848729,
                                "byte_stop": 882688,
                                "text": "Thus, the term \u0022cocaine base\u0022 serves to delineate the precise set of substances subject to the higher penalties."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 194.537,
                                "stop": 201.503,
                                "byte_start": 882688,
                                "byte_stop": 910482,
                                "text": "As we explain in our opinion, we are also not convinced by DePierre\u0027s additional arguments."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 201.503,
                                "stop": 216.34,
                                "byte_start": 910482,
                                "byte_stop": 969832,
                                "text": "We do not agree that reading cocaine base in clause (iii) to mean chemically basic cocaine, renders superfluous, the word \u0022cocaine\u0022 used elsewhere in the statute, nor does our interpretation produce an absurd result."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 216.34,
                                "stop": 228.397,
                                "byte_start": 969832,
                                "byte_stop": 1018107,
                                "text": "We are also not persuaded by DePierre\u0027s suggestion that when Congress enacted this provision, it was all -- it was solely concerned with the special dangers produced by crack cocaine."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 228.397,
                                "stop": 244.173,
                                "byte_start": 1018107,
                                "byte_stop": 1081219,
                                "text": "And finally, the fact that the United States Sentencing Commission has defined cocaine as used in the Federal Sentencing Guidelines to mean \u0022crack cocaine,\u0022 does not mean that the statute in this case must be interpreted in the same way."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 244.173,
                                "stop": 252.744,
                                "byte_start": 1081219,
                                "byte_stop": 1115491,
                                "text": "In some, we hold that the term \u0022cocaine base\u0022 as used in 841 (b) (1), means chemically basic cocaine."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 252.744,
                                "stop": 256.836,
                                "byte_start": 1115491,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The judgment of the United States Court of Appeals for the First Circuit is affirmed."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
